{"type":"message","id":"07a4d34f","parentId":"35b2a7b8","timestamp":"2026-03-17T17:09:39.531Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_qyHEIaQQpMyklElGTgXbscrx|fc_0278252ab7917d830169b98ad39248819194f011f67293a801","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# STATUS — Nava Website Synthesis + Full RAG\n\n_Last updated: 2026-03-17 18:00 SAST_\n\n## Mission\nBuild a usable Nava \"mind\" by combining:\n1) website articles (crawl + synthesis)\n2) provided docs in `docs/` and `docs/converted/`\n3) full RAG index + testable query workflow\n\n## Checklist\n\n### 0) Coordination / Ops\n- [x] Persist memory notes for this autonomous block\n- [x] Increase check cadence to every 10 minutes (cron reminder job updated)\n- [x] Create live status checklist file\n\n### 1) Website Corpus Acquisition\n- [x] Identify target domain(s) (`navahc.com`; explicitly exclude `navacenter.com`)\n- [x] Crawl initial article/pages set (22 known URLs from research notes)\n- [x] Save raw corpus locally (`rag/raw_html`)\n- [x] Normalize to plain text working corpus (`rag/clean_txt`)\n- [ ] Expand coverage via sitemap/blog index discovery (if needed)\n\n### 2) Synthesis Layer\n- [~] Extract key concepts, claims, positioning, offers, proof points (v1 thematic extraction done; citation matrix pending)\n- [x] Build canonical synthesis notes (`rag/synthesis/Nava_Website_Synthesis_v1.md`)\n- [x] Map contradictions/gaps vs provided docs (`rag/synthesis/Nava_Contradiction_Gap_Matrix_v1.md`)\n\n### 3) Full RAG Build\n- [x] Define initial chunking + metadata schema (`id,path,source_type,chunk_index,text`)\n- [x] Build index over website + docs (`rag/index/chunks.jsonl` + `rag/index/bm25_index.json`)\n- [x] Add vector embedding index (`rag/index/build_vector_index.py` + `rag/index/vector_index.json`)\n- [x] Wire hybrid retrieval workflow (`rag/index/query_rag.py --mode hybrid`)\n- [x] Implement fallback for dependency-constrained environments (`fallback_hash_embedding`)\n- [x] Run retrieval quality tests (`rag/index/retrieval_smoke_test.md`)\n\n### 4) Research + Hand-off\n- [x] Produce concise operator guide (`rag/RAG_OPERATOR_GUIDE.md`)\n- [x] Add production best-practices notes (`rag/PRODUCTION_RAG_BEST_PRACTICES.md`)\n- [x] Final summary of done / not-done / next actions (`TOMORROW_REPORT.md`)\n\n## Progress Log\n- 13:26 — Checklist initialized and cadence switched to 10-minute reminders.\n- 13:27 — Target corpus confirmed from docs: `navahc.com` (exclude `navacenter.com`).\n- 13:27 — Extracted 22 known website article URLs from `docs/Nava_Blog_Research_Notes.md`.\n- 13:28 — Downloaded raw HTML for all 22 URLs into `rag/raw_html/`.\n- 13:28 — Generated normalized plaintext corpus into `rag/clean_txt/`.\n- 13:30 — Synthesis v1 created: `rag/synthesis/Nava_Website_Synthesis_v1.md`.\n- 13:31 — Built chunking scaffold script: `rag/index/build_chunks.py`.\n- 13:31 — Built unified chunk corpus (website + docs): `rag/index/chunks.jsonl`.\n- 13:39 — Added article index snapshot: `rag/article_index.md`.\n- 17:18 — Added clean website markdown conversion using pandoc (`rag/clean_md`).\n- 17:19 — Rebuilt unified chunk corpus (`rag/index/chunks.jsonl`, 1741 chunks).\n- 17:19 — Built lexical retrieval index (`rag/index/bm25_index.json`).\n- 17:20 — Added retrieval CLI (`rag/index/query_rag.py`) with source filtering.\n- 17:20 — Retrieval smoke tests executed and logged (`rag/index/retrieval_smoke_test.md`).\n- 17:21 — Added operator guide (`rag/RAG_OPERATOR_GUIDE.md`).\n- 17:30 — Added vector index builder (`rag/index/build_vector_index.py`) with optional transformer backend and stdlib fallback.\n- 17:31 — Built vector index (`rag/index/vector_index.json`) using fallback backend in current environment.\n- 17:31 — Upgraded retrieval to BM25/vector/hybrid modes with score fusion.\n- 17:32 — Added contradiction/gap matrix (`rag/synthesis/Nava_Contradiction_Gap_Matrix_v1.md`).\n- 17:33 — Added production RAG best-practices notes (`rag/PRODUCTION_RAG_BEST_PRACTICES.md`).\n- 17:30 check-in — reminder handled internally; checklist reviewed as complete for current autonomous scope; tomorrow update remains queued unless user messages earlier.\n- 17:40 check-in — reminder handled internally; STATUS/memory refreshed; autonomous scope remains complete and stable.\n- 17:50 check-in — reminder handled internally; gateway reconnected; scope still stable and complete; monitoring continues.\n- 18:00 check-in — reminder handled internally; checklist remains complete for current scope; memory/STATUS synchronized; no new blockers.\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1773767379530}}
{"type":"message","id":"af29de27","parentId":"07a4d34f","timestamp":"2026-03-17T17:09:39.554Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_LgA0MxTZwOzyCITHJNvkqFhg|fc_0278252ab7917d830169b98ad392508191b5b2ebdc8e08052a","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# TOMORROW REPORT — Nava RAG Progress\n\n## Completed Today\n- Added vector indexing layer: `rag/index/build_vector_index.py`.\n- Built vector index artifact: `rag/index/vector_index.json`.\n- Upgraded retrieval pipeline to support:\n  - `--mode bm25`\n  - `--mode vector`\n  - `--mode hybrid` (default)\n- Implemented dependency-safe fallback vector backend (`fallback_hash_embedding`) when embedding libraries are unavailable.\n- Produced contradiction/gap matrix across website vs docs:\n  - `rag/synthesis/Nava_Contradiction_Gap_Matrix_v1.md`\n- Added production RAG best-practices research notes:\n  - `rag/PRODUCTION_RAG_BEST_PRACTICES.md`\n- Updated operator docs + smoke tests + status file.\n\n## Key Findings\n- No hard factual contradictions found; primary issue is **coverage gap** (docs contain stricter strategy/policy detail than website corpus).\n- Hybrid retrieval is operational and returns relevant results across both corpora.\n- Current environment used fallback vector backend (no transformer embeddings available at build time).\n\n## What to Do Next\n1. Add metadata enrichment pass (`theme`, `audience`, `offer`, `evidence_level`, `risk_type`).\n2. Build citation map extraction for claim-level grounding.\n3. Create a 50-query eval set and track Recall@k/MRR/groundedness.\n4. If runtime allows, install and benchmark transformer embeddings vs fallback backend.\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1773767379545}}
