ONNX) in `rag/.venv`.\n- Updated vector build/query pipeline:\n  - `rag/index/build_vector_index.py` now tries `fastembed` -> `ollama_embed` -> fallback hash.\n  - `rag/index/query_rag.py` now query-encodes for `fastembed` and `ollama_embed` backends.\n- Rebuilt index successfully:\n  - `rag/index/vector_index.json` now built with backend `fastembed`.\n- Verified hybrid retrieval works with transformer vectors.\n\n## Skills Research (Safe-first)\nI reviewed current available/ready skills and ClawHub search results for your workflow (LinkedIn/X/content monitoring).\n\n### Already ready now\n- `healthcheck`\n- `session-logs`\n- `skill-creator`\n- `tmux`\n- `weather`\n\n### High-utility candidates for your job (but not auto-installed tonight)\n- `summarize` — strong for turning long sources/video/articles into content inputs.\n- `xurl` (or equivalent X API skill) — useful once authenticated for X execution workflows.\n- `blogwatcher`/RSS monitor type skills — useful for trend intake and content trigger pipelines.\n\n### Why I did **not** auto-install from ClawHub yet\n- Community skills vary in trust and maintenance quality.\n- I want to run a stricter risk screen first (publisher reputation, code inspection, external-write scope, dependency footprint).\n- You explicitly asked to avoid risky skills, so I’m defaulting conservative.\n\n## Recommendation\n- Keep current pipeline with `fastembed` as production default for now.\n- Tomorrow morning: I’ll brief you with a shortlist of **secure** install candidates and a “safe install order” based on your Nava + LinkedIn/X workflow.\n"},"partialJson":"{\"file_path\":\"TOMORROW_REPORT.md\",\"content\":\"# TOMORROW REPORT — Nava RAG + Skills Research\\n\\n## Completed Tonight\\n- Retried transformer upgrade with GPU-aware path.\\n- Attempted `sentence-transformers` install first; blocked by very large CUDA wheel + intermittent network.\\n- Implemented a more reliable transformer route with `fastembed` (ONNX) in `rag/.venv`.\\n- Updated vector build/query pipeline:\\n  - `rag/index/build_vector_index.py` now tries `fastembed` -> `ollama_embed` -> fallback hash.\\n  - `rag/index/query_rag.py` now query-encodes for `fastembed` and `ollama_embed` backends.\\n- Rebuilt index successfully:\\n  - `rag/index/vector_index.json` now built with backend `fastembed`.\\n- Verified hybrid retrieval works with transformer vectors.\\n\\n## Skills Research (Safe-first)\\nI reviewed current available/ready skills and ClawHub search results for your workflow (LinkedIn/X/content monitoring).\\n\\n### Already ready now\\n- `healthcheck`\\n- `session-logs`\\n- `skill-creator`\\n- `tmux`\\n- `weather`\\n\\n### High-utility candidates for your job (but not auto-installed tonight)\\n- `summarize` — strong for turning long sources/video/articles into content inputs.\\n- `xurl` (or equivalent X API skill) — useful once authenticated for X execution workflows.\\n- `blogwatcher`/RSS monitor type skills — useful for trend intake and content trigger pipelines.\\n\\n### Why I did **not** auto-install from ClawHub yet\\n- Community skills vary in trust and maintenance quality.\\n- I want to run a stricter risk screen first (publisher reputation, code inspection, external-write scope, dependency footprint).\\n- You explicitly asked to avoid risky skills, so I’m defaulting conservative.\\n\\n## Recommendation\\n- Keep current pipeline with `fastembed` as production default for now.\\n- Tomorrow morning: I’ll brief you with a shortlist of **secure** install candidates and a “safe install order” based on your Nava + LinkedIn/X workflow.\\n\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.3-codex","usage":{"input":741,"output":517,"cacheRead":73344,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":74602,"cost":{"input":0.00129675,"output":0.007238,"cacheRead":0.0128352,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.02136995}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773767413786}}
